<br />
In the coming years, health care costs for the elderly will easily dwarf any other government expenditures.  Imagine how much could be saved if people simply were discouraged, or prevented, from smoking.  If a smoker lived in isolation such that their actions didn't affect anyone else, it wouldn't be much of an issue.  But that is not the case as everyone pays for it in the end (through taxes).  It's definitely a societal issue.</div>
