Let me simplify it for you:<br />
<br />
If a smoker isn't fucking up the air around anyone, let them smoke.<br />
<br />
No one here claims cigarettes are healthy that I recall, simply that the numbers hyped by anti tobacco industry are exagerrated.  Please link us to the critieria your reports use to determine the link between cigarettes and form of death.  Again, no one is saying that cigarettes don't cause lung cancer.  Most simply want a statement that says &quot;If a person smoked X amount of cigarettes or more and got lung cancer, then that case of lung cancer is considered caused by cigarette smoking&quot;<br />
<br />
The notion that there are people in america that smoke and don't know the risks is absurd.<br />
<br />
The notion that we have some sort of responsibility to save these people from themselves is even more absurd.<br />
<br />
Maybe the above will help stifle some of the petty nitpicking about cliche propaganda.that has been shoved down our throats for like 15+ years.<br />
<br />
IMO, the advertising isn't even required.  Fuck the smokers.  When you first puff a cig, you cough your fucking lungs out.  That's your body saying &quot;HEY FUCKER, I DON'T LIKE THAT!&quot;  If you choose to do it after that, then hey, more power to you.  If touching a hot stove gave people orgasms, would we have some sort of government initiative setup to inform people that hot stoves will burn our fucking hands off if we continue to touch them?</div>
